Setup the jSS7 simulator
========================
Chapter 12. SS7 Simulator
ss7/docs/en-US/pdf/Mobicents_SS7Stack_User_Guide.pdf
ansible/files/mobicents-ss7-2.0.0.FINAL.zip

$ ansible-playbook setup-jss7.yml -i hosts

# Tab 1
$ vagrant ssh server
[INSIDE]
$ cd /opt/jSS7/ss7/mobicents-ss7-simulator
$ sudo bin/run.sh core --name=dsi-test-server --rmi=9999 --http=8888

Go to http://192.168.200.101:8888/

SS7_Simulator_dsi-test-client -> type=TesterHost -> Press `start' button
http://10.10.0.155:8888/InvokeAction//SS7_Simulator_dsi-test-client%3Atype%3DTesterHost/action=start?action=start
http://10.10.0.155:8888/InvokeAction//SS7_Simulator_dsi-test-client%3Atype%3DTesterHost/action=stop?action=stop

# Tab 2
$ vagrant ssh client
[INSIDE]
$ cd /opt/jSS7/ss7/mobicents-ss7-simulator
$ sudo bin/run.sh gui --name=dsi-test-server

Select `Connect to the existing testerHost...'
service:jmx:rmi:///jndi/rmi://server:9999/server
Press `Run tests'
Press `Start'

# Tab 3
$ vagrant ssh client
[INSIDE]
$ cd /opt/jSS7/ss7/mobicents-ss7-simulator
$ sudo bin/run.sh gui --name=dsi-test-client

Select `Create a local testerHost'
Press `Run tests'
Press `Start'

We have connection established!
